WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:44.795 --> 00:00:46.754
(DOG BARKING)

2
00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:56.139
(TRAIN HORN WHISTLING
IN THE DISTANCE)

3
00:01:08.986 --> 00:01:11.821
Miss. I wanna go home.

4
00:01:12.364 --> 00:01:16.784
Yeah. I'll be out of your hair in a minute.
I got a flight to catch.

5
00:01:20.372 --> 00:01:22.665
That's it. I got it.

6
00:01:23.208 --> 00:01:26.335
WOMAN ON PA: Welcome to Wichita
Mid-Continent Airport.

7
00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:30.882
Convenient. friendly. affordable.
Fly with us.

8
00:01:35.220 --> 00:01:40.349
Please note. the Kansas Clean Air Act has
designated this airport as non-smoking.

9
00:01:51.695 --> 00:01:55.323
Your attention. please.
Baggage claim is located

10
00:01:55.407 --> 00:01:57.366
on the east side of the terminal.

11
00:01:57.451 --> 00:01:59.827
Hotel and ground transportation
information boards

12
00:01:59.912 --> 00:02:04.373
and public telephones are located
opposite the baggage carousels.

13
00:02:19.139 --> 00:02:21.974
Ladies and gentlemen.
please maintain visual contact

14
00:02:22.059 --> 00:02:24.644
with your personal property at all times.

15
00:02:24.728 --> 00:02:29.065
Please do not leave your baggage
or other items unattended.

16
00:02:29.149 --> 00:02:31.400
Thank you for your cooperation.

17
00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:00.429
- MAN: Excuse me.
- Sorry.

18
00:03:00.514 --> 00:03:03.224
So. I'm gonna make it
onto the earlier flight. right?

19
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:04.517
Are you gonna check that?

20
00:03:04.601 --> 00:03:06.561
No. I'm gonna carry it on.
It's got valuables in it.

21
00:03:06.645 --> 00:03:07.645
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

22
00:03:29.418 --> 00:03:30.960
- God. excuse me.
- No. I'm sorry.

23
00:03:33.088 --> 00:03:34.297
That bag is wicked heavy. anyhow.

24
00:03:34.381 --> 00:03:36.924
I was looking at my phone.
I hate it when people do that.

25
00:03:41.138 --> 00:03:42.972
You have a little

26
00:03:44.308 --> 00:03:45.766
smudge.

27
00:03:58.655 --> 00:03:59.697
What are these?

28
00:03:59.781 --> 00:04:03.451
Those are two barrel carburetors
for a Pontiac Tri-Power.

29
00:04:08.665 --> 00:04:11.500
Those are exhaust tips for a '74 Z-28.

30
00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:15.546
I restore old cars. so...

31
00:04:18.300 --> 00:04:20.635
Hair-dryer. (LAUGHS)

32
00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:30.853
(EXCLAIMS) Oh. my God. I'm so sorry.

33
00:04:34.024 --> 00:04:36.400
- This is getting to be a habit.
- (CHUCKLING) Yeah. it is.

34
00:04:38.654 --> 00:04:40.321
Sorry about that.

35
00:04:41.031 --> 00:04:42.531
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

36
00:04:44.326 --> 00:04:45.785
- Thank you.
- Yeah. sure.

37
00:04:45.869 --> 00:04:48.287
- Boston?
- Yeah.

38
00:04:49.039 --> 00:04:50.164
Gate 12.

39
00:04:52.209 --> 00:04:53.751
- Enjoy your flight. Mr. Garcia.
- Thank you.

40
00:04:53.835 --> 00:04:54.877
Hi.

41
00:04:56.338 --> 00:04:57.922
I'm sorry. You're not on this flight.

42
00:04:58.840 --> 00:05:00.925
Well. I just checked in
for this one. like. 10 minutes ago.

43
00:05:01.009 --> 00:05:02.468
That must be some sort of mistake.

44
00:05:02.552 --> 00:05:04.720
I'm sorry.
the computer shows that we're booked.

45
00:05:04.805 --> 00:05:06.639
Listen. Sharry.

46
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:09.642
Tomorrow my little sister's
getting married. I practically raised her.

47
00:05:09.726 --> 00:05:11.727
SHARRY: I'm sorry.
we are completely sold out.

48
00:05:11.812 --> 00:05:15.189
JUNE: Listen. can you help me out
for a second? She's my little sister.

49
00:05:15.273 --> 00:05:16.565
She's April. I'm June.

50
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:18.651
she's counting on me
to march her down the aisle tomorrow.

51
00:05:18.735 --> 00:05:20.111
That's very sweet.

52
00:05:20.195 --> 00:05:22.822
but the 11:50 will get you there
tomorrow morning with plenty of time.

53
00:05:23.365 --> 00:05:25.449
Your boarding pass. sir?

54
00:05:27.244 --> 00:05:29.412
Sometimes things happen for a reason.

55
00:05:31.289 --> 00:05:34.208
- Enjoy your flight. Mr. Miller.
- Thank you.

56
00:05:34.918 --> 00:05:38.337
WOMAN ON PA: This is the final
boarding call for US Midland Air. flight 77

57
00:05:38.422 --> 00:05:42.591
non-stop service to Boston's
Logan Airport. now boarding at gate 12.

58
00:05:42.676 --> 00:05:45.261
Would all passengers holding
a valid boarding pass. please proceed...

59
00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:49.765
I should've seen it coming. boss.
He went on tilt. he came undone.

60
00:05:49.850 --> 00:05:52.351
Coming undone in our business
means you need a margarita.

61
00:05:52.436 --> 00:05:55.646
It doesn't mean capping a dozen people
in a government lab and blowing it up.

62
00:05:55.731 --> 00:05:58.190
It doesn't mean stealing an object
of critical importance.

63
00:05:58.275 --> 00:06:00.818
- Does he have the Zephyr or not?
- We believe so.

64
00:06:01.653 --> 00:06:04.488
Uh-huh. You believe so.

65
00:06:04.573 --> 00:06:07.032
- (WHISPERING) Check it out.
- I don't care what you believe. Fitz.

66
00:06:07.117 --> 00:06:09.118
- I need you to clean your mess up.
- Go back and play it again.

67
00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:10.327
I want the Zephyr.

68
00:06:10.412 --> 00:06:12.830
We'll have it in hand
by the time he lands in Boston.

69
00:06:14.374 --> 00:06:16.167
Find out who and what she is.

70
00:06:16.251 --> 00:06:18.711
Should I have the field office pick her up
in Wichita?

71
00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:21.130
Mmm-mmm. I got a better idea.

72
00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:27.470
Miss Havens? We did find a seat for you.

73
00:06:27.679 --> 00:06:28.804
(LOUIE LOUIE RINGTONE PLAYING)

74
00:06:28.889 --> 00:06:30.765
MALE ATTENDANT ON PA:
I'd like to have your attention. please.

75
00:06:30.849 --> 00:06:32.016
We apologize for the delay.

76
00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:35.060
We will be departing
Wichita Airport shortly.

77
00:06:35.645 --> 00:06:37.396
Thanks for your patience.

78
00:06:41.276 --> 00:06:43.694
JUNE: I know it's policy or whatever
and it's just your job.

79
00:06:43.779 --> 00:06:46.655
- but it's kind of lame.
- SHARRY: Again. I apologize.

80
00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:49.116
Fitz. What did you do?

81
00:06:52.621 --> 00:06:55.998
It's no wonder these airlines
are going out of business.

82
00:06:56.082 --> 00:06:58.000
ATTENDANT: We have been cleared
onto the runway.

83
00:06:58.084 --> 00:06:59.543
There's nobody on the plane.

84
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.721
MALE ATTENDANT: The captain has
turned on the "fasten seatbelt" sign.

85
00:07:10.806 --> 00:07:13.140
Please remain seated
until the sign has been turned off

86
00:07:13.225 --> 00:07:15.559
and it's safe to move about the cabin.

87
00:07:16.353 --> 00:07:18.020
I'm June. by the way.

88
00:07:18.104 --> 00:07:19.688
I'm Roy Miller.

89
00:07:20.023 --> 00:07:22.191
- Nice to meet you.
- It's very nice to meet you.

90
00:07:24.069 --> 00:07:25.236
STEWARDESS: Tequila on the rocks?

91
00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:27.488
Yeah. Just in time. thanks.

92
00:07:30.867 --> 00:07:33.828
So. your sister's
getting married tomorrow?

93
00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:35.830
- Excuse me?
- Your sister.

94
00:07:35.914 --> 00:07:37.665
She's getting married tomorrow.
Congratulations.

95
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:39.625
Oh. Yeah. thanks.

96
00:07:44.673 --> 00:07:48.217
You know. Roy. I'm a bad liar.

97
00:07:48.301 --> 00:07:50.261
I'm sorry. how's that?

98
00:07:50.345 --> 00:07:53.097
April is getting married.
but not till Saturday.

99
00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:54.390
You had me fooled.

100
00:07:54.474 --> 00:07:59.895
Well. I do have a fitting tomorrow.
So. I do. actually. have to go home.

101
00:08:07.696 --> 00:08:09.780
I hope this isn't gonna be a rough flight.

102
00:08:13.994 --> 00:08:15.452
(MUTTERING) It might be.

103
00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:21.000
Wichita is a long way to go
for a carburetor.

104
00:08:21.084 --> 00:08:23.544
It's not just any carburetor.
It's a triple deuce.

105
00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:26.005
- Oh.
- I'm restoring a '66 GTO.

106
00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:28.507
And Kansas has the best scrap.

107
00:08:28.592 --> 00:08:29.800
Really?

108
00:08:29.885 --> 00:08:31.427
My dad had a garage.

109
00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:34.346
and when I was a kid.
he bought this chassis.

110
00:08:34.431 --> 00:08:38.434
He used to take us to yards.
and search for parts. you know?

111
00:08:38.894 --> 00:08:40.144
He died in '98.

112
00:08:40.228 --> 00:08:45.608
and now that April's getting married.
I just figured. why not finish it up.

113
00:08:45.692 --> 00:08:47.902
give it to her sort of as a wedding present?

114
00:08:48.612 --> 00:08:52.364
Kind of like a present
from our dad. too. you know?

115
00:08:52.449 --> 00:08:54.116
That's nice.

116
00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:55.951
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

117
00:09:05.712 --> 00:09:06.879
I used to think that

118
00:09:06.963 --> 00:09:08.797
(SIGHS)

119
00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:13.802
Someday. when the last part went in.

120
00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:18.140
I would just climb into that GTO
and start it up.

121
00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:22.728
Just drive and drive and drive.
and just keep driving

122
00:09:22.812 --> 00:09:26.148
until I got to the tip of South America.

123
00:09:27.150 --> 00:09:30.110
- Cape Horn.
- Yeah.

124
00:09:30.779 --> 00:09:34.073
- There's beautiful islands down there.
- Yeah?

125
00:09:34.157 --> 00:09:35.950
- Pirate islands.
- (LAUGHS)

126
00:09:39.788 --> 00:09:42.206
Yeah. "someday."
That's a dangerous word.

127
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:43.832
Dangerous?

128
00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:48.045
It's really just code for "never."

129
00:09:50.966 --> 00:09:54.176
I think a lot about things I haven't done.

130
00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:58.347
Dive in the Great Barrier Reef.
Ride the Orient Express.

131
00:09:59.140 --> 00:10:03.519
Live on the Amalfi Coast with nothing
but a motorcycle and a backpack.

132
00:10:04.354 --> 00:10:07.481
Kiss a stranger on the balcony
of the Hotel Du Cap.

133
00:10:10.443 --> 00:10:11.610
Where is that?

134
00:10:11.695 --> 00:10:13.570
South of France.

135
00:10:14.781 --> 00:10:15.990
Hmm.

136
00:10:17.033 --> 00:10:20.369
What about you? What's your list?

137
00:10:21.871 --> 00:10:25.207
Well. yours sounds pretty good.

138
00:10:29.212 --> 00:10:30.462
Wow.

139
00:10:32.632 --> 00:10:33.632
Thanks.

140
00:10:34.217 --> 00:10:35.718
It's no problem.

141
00:10:37.220 --> 00:10:39.596
I'll just put this up here. if that's all right.

142
00:10:43.852 --> 00:10:45.978
JUNE: You know what?

143
00:10:46.062 --> 00:10:49.106
I'm gonna go back and use the restroom.

144
00:10:50.400 --> 00:10:52.484
- I'll help you.
- Thanks.

145
00:11:00.076 --> 00:11:02.161
Lots of turbulence. huh?

146
00:11:07.459 --> 00:11:09.960
- I'll be out in a minute.
- Sure.

147
00:11:14.007 --> 00:11:15.090
(GRUNTS)

148
00:11:15.175 --> 00:11:16.508
(SCREAMING)

149
00:11:20.388 --> 00:11:23.891
"Kiss a stranger on the balcony
of the Hotel Du Cap"?

150
00:11:23.975 --> 00:11:25.642
I mean. what kind of a line is that?

151
00:11:31.608 --> 00:11:35.444
I mean. it's. like. a really good line.

152
00:11:40.825 --> 00:11:42.326
Ma'am? Ma'am?

153
00:11:51.503 --> 00:11:53.504
Did you see his hands. by any chance?

154
00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:56.298
They just. like. snatched that bag
right out of the air.

155
00:11:56.382 --> 00:11:58.300
Lightning-fast reflexes.

156
00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:03.138
Not cool.

157
00:12:06.476 --> 00:12:07.768
Okay.

158
00:12:08.228 --> 00:12:09.228
(CHECKS HER BREATH)

159
00:12:25.036 --> 00:12:26.036
Huh?

160
00:12:28.248 --> 00:12:29.832
This will help.

161
00:12:42.887 --> 00:12:44.388
Ocupado.

162
00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:48.100
Enough. It's over. Roy.

163
00:12:48.560 --> 00:12:51.061
Yeah. I agree. Enough.

164
00:12:51.146 --> 00:12:52.896
Where's the Zephyr?

165
00:13:12.917 --> 00:13:16.086
Why is the girl on the plane? Tell me.

166
00:13:16.171 --> 00:13:17.963
Why did Fitz put her on the plane?

167
00:13:18.256 --> 00:13:19.965
(SILENCED PISTOL FIRING)

168
00:13:20.925 --> 00:13:22.509
Don't move. Miller.

169
00:13:31.686 --> 00:13:33.228
(ENGINES WHINING)

170
00:13:34.189 --> 00:13:36.857
So what are you gonna do?
What are you gonna do?

171
00:13:36.941 --> 00:13:39.735
You're just gonna
let this opportunity pass you by?

172
00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:40.819
No. of course you're not.

173
00:13:40.904 --> 00:13:43.197
You're gonna walk right through that door.
you're gonna get it right.

174
00:13:43.281 --> 00:13:44.615
It's not your first rodeo. woman.

175
00:13:58.338 --> 00:13:59.379
(SOFTLY) Hey.

176
00:14:07.805 --> 00:14:09.431
I decided to join you.

177
00:14:36.459 --> 00:14:38.585
I'm sorry. I...

178
00:14:38.670 --> 00:14:41.713
- No. no. don't... It's great.
- I'm sorry.

179
00:14:41.798 --> 00:14:43.757
It's just. like. the tequila and the altitude
and everything.

180
00:14:43.841 --> 00:14:45.175
There's something I've gotta tell you.

181
00:14:45.260 --> 00:14:48.804
What? Oh. my God.
you're in a relationship. I'm so sorry.

182
00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:51.390
No. no. no. That's not it.

183
00:14:51.474 --> 00:14:54.434
Okay. I'm all ears. What is it?

184
00:14:57.814 --> 00:14:58.981
Are we landing?

185
00:14:59.691 --> 00:15:01.525
No. not yet. Uh...

186
00:15:03.194 --> 00:15:04.403
No?

187
00:15:04.487 --> 00:15:07.906
Listen. there's no need to panic. I have

188
00:15:09.158 --> 00:15:10.659
contained the situation.

189
00:15:11.661 --> 00:15:13.328
Situation?

190
00:15:13.997 --> 00:15:17.416
Yeah. We've lost the pilots.

191
00:15:19.002 --> 00:15:22.504
- Where did they go?
- I mean. they're dead.

192
00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:24.464
- The pilots are dead.
- Shot. It's...

193
00:15:24.549 --> 00:15:26.091
Shot?

194
00:15:28.469 --> 00:15:29.720
By who?

195
00:15:31.055 --> 00:15:32.097
(CRUNCHING ICE)

196
00:15:32.181 --> 00:15:34.349
Well. me.

197
00:15:34.976 --> 00:15:36.935
Actually. I shot the first pilot.

198
00:15:37.020 --> 00:15:40.689
He shot the second pilot accidentally.
It's just

199
00:15:43.693 --> 00:15:45.736
one of those things.

200
00:15:48.406 --> 00:15:49.948
(LAUGHING)

201
00:16:02.211 --> 00:16:04.713
Seriously. this is great!

202
00:16:05.214 --> 00:16:08.550
Really. I'm relieved
you are taking this so well.

203
00:16:14.223 --> 00:16:15.307
Where are you going?

204
00:16:15.391 --> 00:16:18.352
I'm just gonna go check on things
and think about landing.

205
00:16:18.436 --> 00:16:20.687
Would you mind
putting your seatbelt on for me?

206
00:16:20.772 --> 00:16:22.147
- That would be great.
- Yeah.

207
00:16:22.315 --> 00:16:24.232
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

208
00:16:37.580 --> 00:16:39.373
This is weird.

209
00:16:39.457 --> 00:16:41.124
(PA BEEPS)

210
00:16:41.751 --> 00:16:43.502
(ENGINES WHINING)

211
00:16:43.836 --> 00:16:45.045
(YELPS)

212
00:16:53.429 --> 00:16:54.554
(SCREAMING)

213
00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:56.765
MILLER: Mayday. Mayday.
This is US Midland Air 77 heavy.

214
00:16:56.849 --> 00:16:59.518
What's happening?
Everybody's dead out there!

215
00:16:59.602 --> 00:17:03.230
Come on in. Sit down.
Mayday. mayday. mayday.

216
00:17:03.314 --> 00:17:05.357
- Everybody's dead in here.
- MILLER: I'm declaring an emergency.

217
00:17:05.441 --> 00:17:07.818
- Oh. my God! Are we going down?
- I'm sorry?

218
00:17:07.902 --> 00:17:09.027
Are we going down?

219
00:17:09.112 --> 00:17:11.405
No. June. it's just a rapid descent.
Please. sit down.

220
00:17:11.489 --> 00:17:13.198
MAN ON RADIO: Please state
your emergency. Midland 77.

221
00:17:13.282 --> 00:17:14.866
I'm sorry.
I think I've heard enough of this guy.

222
00:17:14.951 --> 00:17:17.035
Are you a pilot? Who are you?

223
00:17:17.120 --> 00:17:18.203
The shoulder straps.

224
00:17:18.287 --> 00:17:21.832
You can put those over.
and it clicks in right down there.

225
00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:24.418
You wanna click it right there. that's it.

226
00:17:24.502 --> 00:17:27.546
Okay. I got it. I got it. Okay...

227
00:17:27.630 --> 00:17:28.880
Gear down. showdown.

228
00:17:28.965 --> 00:17:30.799
(LANDING GEAR WHINING)

229
00:17:30.883 --> 00:17:33.176
Why can't we just land in an airport?

230
00:17:33.261 --> 00:17:35.887
No. no. that wouldn't be a good idea.

231
00:17:35.972 --> 00:17:38.640
- They'll be waiting for us.
- What do you mean? Waiting for us?

232
00:17:38.724 --> 00:17:41.393
- Who?
- I think the less you know. the better.

233
00:17:41.477 --> 00:17:42.811
What?

234
00:17:43.479 --> 00:17:45.856
MILLER: Okay. we're gonna
touch down here.

235
00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:48.191
JUNE: Oh. God. Oh. my God!

236
00:17:48.443 --> 00:17:49.901
(JUNE WHIMPERING)

237
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:55.449
- That's a truck. That's a truck!
- Yeah.

238
00:17:55.533 --> 00:17:56.575
- That's a truck!
- Yup.

239
00:17:56.659 --> 00:17:57.742
That's a truck!

240
00:18:02.123 --> 00:18:03.748
JUNE: Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

241
00:18:03.833 --> 00:18:08.253
Here I am
Rock you like a hurricane

242
00:18:08.671 --> 00:18:11.339
- That's a curve. That's a curve!
- I see it. I see it.

243
00:18:13.176 --> 00:18:14.676
(SCREAMING)

244
00:18:18.681 --> 00:18:20.015
Oh. my God!

245
00:18:21.726 --> 00:18:23.185
Oh. God!

246
00:18:30.485 --> 00:18:32.235
(ENGINES POWERING DOWN)

247
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:33.528
