610
00:39:15.103 --> 00:39:18.564
Well. when I said.
"Sometimes things happen for a reason."

611
00:39:20.358 --> 00:39:24.236
That's not a warning.
That's not a warning. Roy!

612
00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:27.739
That's like a needlepoint expression
or a bumper sticker.

613
00:39:27.824 --> 00:39:31.994
Next time. try. "June. if you get
on this plane. you will fucking die!"

614
00:39:32.454 --> 00:39:36.165
Huh? You know. Roy. maybe they meant it
when they said that I would be safe.

615
00:39:37.167 --> 00:39:39.668
- You really mean that. June?
- Yeah!

616
00:39:40.628 --> 00:39:45.340
- Did you feel safe with them?
- Safer than I do now!

617
00:39:45.425 --> 00:39:48.218
Okay. okay. All right.

618
00:39:48.428 --> 00:39:50.929
(TIRES SCREECHING)

619
00:39:54.517 --> 00:39:55.559
(SCREAMING)

620
00:40:12.702 --> 00:40:14.786
Just so you understand.

621
00:40:14.871 --> 00:40:18.707
right now. out there. on your own.
your life expectancy is like here.

622
00:40:18.791 --> 00:40:21.293
With me. it's here. Without me. here.

623
00:40:21.377 --> 00:40:25.255
With me. without me.
With me. without me.

624
00:40:25.340 --> 00:40:26.965
So...

625
00:40:27.050 --> 00:40:30.469
I wouldn't advise going home.
But. you know. it's up to you.

626
00:40:30.553 --> 00:40:32.262
So right now I need another car.
keep moving.

627
00:40:33.223 --> 00:40:35.557
Someone else is depending on me.
Someone whose life is in danger.

628
00:40:35.642 --> 00:40:39.311
Someone who trusts me.
Every second I waste chasing you.

629
00:40:39.854 --> 00:40:42.231
I'm letting him down.

630
00:40:42.732 --> 00:40:44.149
(BEEPING)

631
00:40:44.234 --> 00:40:45.567
