to those shelves over there.

739
00:48:46.632 --> 00:48:47.632
Okay.

740
00:48:47.717 --> 00:48:48.675
- Okay?
- Yeah.

741
00:48:48.759 --> 00:48:50.093
- You ready?
- Yeah.

742
00:48:50.177 --> 00:48:51.386
One...

743
00:48:53.305 --> 00:48:54.973
(JUNE SCREAMING)

744
00:48:55.558 --> 00:48:57.434
Oh. my God!

745
00:48:57.893 --> 00:48:59.936
Sorry. I panicked.

746
00:49:01.480 --> 00:49:04.315
- What number would you like?
- Let's just stick with three. it's good.

747
00:49:04.400 --> 00:49:06.484
Okay. One... Two...

748
00:49:06.569 --> 00:49:07.736
Three.

749
00:49:19.749 --> 00:49:23.043
These guys are fancy. Mags.

750
00:49:23.127 --> 00:49:28.423
Could be Antonio Quintana's men.
He's a Spanish arms dealer.

751
00:49:28.507 --> 00:49:31.468
He also wants the battery.

752
00:49:31.552 --> 00:49:32.510
- Ready?
- Uh-huh.

753
00:49:32.595 --> 00:49:34.512
- Let's move.
- Okay.

754
00:49:36.265 --> 00:49:38.058
June. June!

755
00:49:39.268 --> 00:49:42.645
How the hell are we gonna get out of here?

756
00:49:42.730 --> 00:49:44.314
And where the hell is Simon?

757
00:49:44.398 --> 00:49:45.774
I don't know yet. but he left a message.

758
00:49:45.858 --> 00:49:47.776
- A message?
- Wait.

759
00:49:48.611 --> 00:49:50.612
(MEN SPEAKING SPANISH)

760
00:49:55.117 --> 00:49:57.952
What I need you to do right now
is wait here.

761
00:49:58.037 --> 00:50:00.038
- What?
- Yeah. I'm gonna find us a way out.

762
00:50:00.122 --> 00:50:01.915
- I can't wait here!
- I'll be right back.

763
00:50:01.999 --> 00:50:03.041
Wait! Roy!

764
00:50:03.626 --> 00:50:04.959
Just take this.

765
00:50:07.463 --> 00:50:09.297
- (MACHINE GUNS FIRING)
- (GASPING)

766
00:50:09.673 --> 00:50:11.633
(MEN SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

767
00:50:17.139 --> 00:50:18.723
(WHISPERING) Roy?

768
00:50:19.642 --> 00:50:21.226
Shit.

769
00:50:21.310 --> 00:50:23.019
(WHIMPERING)

770
00:50:23.312 --> 00:50:24.354
June?

771
00:50:24.897 --> 00:50:28.483
- (SCREAMING)
- June! June! June! June!

772
00:50:29.443 --> 00:50:32.320
June! June! June! June!

773
00:50:35.407 --> 00:50:36.449
June!

774
00:50:36.534 --> 00:50:37.909
Please stop saying my name.

775
00:50:37.993 --> 00:50:39.828
You keep saying my name.
it's freaking me out.

776
00:50:41.288 --> 00:50:44.040
- Okay. I understand.
- Okay.

777
00:50:44.291 --> 00:50:46.084
(MEN SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

778
00:50:46.502 --> 00:50:47.585
- Drink this.
- What is it?

779
00:50:47.670 --> 00:50:49.671
Brotine-zero.
They're gonna smoke us with D-5.

780
00:50:49.755 --> 00:50:51.131
Oh. yeah.

781
00:50:53.175 --> 00:50:54.175
Where's yours?

782
00:50:58.055 --> 00:50:59.681
Oh. shit.

783
00:50:59.765 --> 00:51:01.099
- I'm sorry.
- Oh. no.

784
00:51:01.183 --> 00:51:02.517
They're coming.

785
00:51:02.685 --> 00:51:04.352
(MEN SHOUTING)

786
00:51:20.035 --> 00:51:21.035
(WHISPERING) June.

787
00:51:23.372 --> 00:51:26.291
I know this looks bad.

788
00:51:26.375 --> 00:51:29.127
but we'll be out of here

789
00:51:29.211 --> 00:51:32.213
in a couple of minutes.

790
00:51:32.298 --> 00:51:33.423
I got this.

791
00:51:36.135 --> 00:51:37.552
(GRUNTS)

792
00:51:38.929 --> 00:51:41.681
We gotta go. June. Here. I'll help you.

793
00:51:43.392 --> 00:51:45.768
(AIRPLANE ENGINES WHINING)

794
00:51:49.148 --> 00:51:50.815
(ALARMS BEEPING)

795
00:51:52.276 --> 00:51:53.693
(SHOUTING) We've been hit!

796
00:51:53.777 --> 00:51:55.987
But it's okay!

797
00:51:56.071 --> 00:51:58.489
We get through this. we're home free!

798
00:51:58.574 --> 00:52:01.159
Ready. set. go!

799
00:52:01.660 --> 00:52:03.494
(PARACHUTE OPENING)

800
00:52:13.047 --> 00:52:15.089
We're almost there.

801
00:52:20.262 --> 00:52:21.846
(WAVES LAPPING)

802
00:52:27.269 --> 00:52:28.937
(MOANS GROGGILY)

803
00:52:36.028 --> 00:52:37.904
(BIRDS TWITTERING)

804
00:53:01.053 --> 00:53:02.470
Hey. there. sleepy head.

805
00:53:12.356 --> 00:53:13.481
How long have I been out?

806
00:53:14.108 --> 00:53:15.900
Eighteen hours.

807
00:53:17.778 --> 00:53:19.654
Where am I?

808
00:53:20.531 --> 00:53:22.532
My place.

809
00:53:24.326 --> 00:53:25.326
We're off-grid.

810
00:53:26.412 --> 00:53:27.870
No one's ever found me here.

811
00:53:28.372 --> 00:53:31.332
Shame we can't stay longer.
We got a rendezvous with Simon.

812
00:53:31.417 --> 00:53:34.335
He's fine. I figured out his code.

813
00:53:35.337 --> 00:53:36.754
He's crazy about trains.

814
00:53:36.839 --> 00:53:39.590
He used the passport I gave him
and went to Austria.

815
00:53:39.675 --> 00:53:40.800
You drugged me again. Roy.

816
00:53:42.011 --> 00:53:43.177
Yeah.

817
00:53:44.013 --> 00:53:45.221
You can't do that.

818
00:53:46.807 --> 00:53:49.600
Well. you weren't coping well.

819
00:53:49.685 --> 00:53:53.688
I'm not sure. if you were awake.
if they would've even let you live.

820
00:53:54.523 --> 00:53:55.523
What am I wearing?

821
00:53:57.067 --> 00:53:58.359
- Huh?
- Huh?

822
00:54:00.195 --> 00:54:02.447
A bikini. We're in the tropics.

823
00:54:02.531 --> 00:54:04.699
How did I get in the bikini?

824
00:54:08.495 --> 00:54:12.665
June. I've been trained
to dismantle a bomb in the pitch black

825
00:54:12.750 --> 00:54:16.419
with nothing but a safety pin
and a Junior Mint.

826
00:54:16.503 --> 00:54:20.089
I think I can get you in and out
of some clothes without

827
00:54:21.091 --> 00:54:22.216
looking.

828
00:54:26.263 --> 00:54:28.723
I'm not saying that's what I did. but...

829
00:54:28.807 --> 00:54:31.851
- (GRUNTS)
- Okay. Sorry. Reflex.

830
00:54:32.519 --> 00:54:35.271
I deserved that. Hit me again.

831
00:54:35.356 --> 00:54:37.190
I won't stop you.

832
00:54:38.942 --> 00:54:39.984
June.

833
00:54:42.404 --> 00:54:43.446
June?

834
00:54:45.949 --> 00:54:47.075
June!

835
00:54:48.410 --> 00:54:50.828
...paper clips and Junior Mints...

836
00:54:53.957 --> 00:54:55.958
"Not that I'm saying that's what I did."

837
00:54:58.962 --> 00:55:00.088
Shit!

838
00:55:03.258 --> 00:55:05.551
(LOUIE LOUIE RINGTONE PLAYING)

839
00:55:06.095 --> 00:55:07.804
Is this his phone?

840
00:55:12.267 --> 00:55:13.726
Movement alert.

841
00:55:15.312 --> 00:55:16.896
5826

842
00:55:17.564 --> 00:55:18.773
Amapola.

843
00:55:20.651 --> 00:55:22.610
That's a '67 Grand Prix.

844
00:55:23.153 --> 00:55:24.654
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

845
00:55:31.495 --> 00:55:33.788
I thought we were off the grid.

846
00:55:34.415 --> 00:55:35.581
April.

847
00:55:36.125 --> 00:55:37.291
April?

848
00:55:37.835 --> 00:55:42.547
April! I know! No. I'm okay!
Listen. April... April? April?

849
00:55:43.340 --> 00:55:45.925
April. can you hear me? April!

850
00:55:46.677 --> 00:55:48.344
April. can you...

851
00:55:50.806 --> 00:55:53.099
(OUT OF RANGE TONE SOUNDING)

852
00:55:57.229 --> 00:55:59.772
JUNE ON RECORDING: I know!
No. I'm okay! Listen. April... April?

853
00:55:59.857 --> 00:56:02.150
April. can you hear me? April!

854
00:56:02.609 --> 00:56:03.901
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

855
00:56:03.986 --> 00:56:05.194
We don't know. Antonio.

856
00:56:05.279 --> 00:56:08.698
We traced her phone to the Azores.
We're in range now.

857
00:56:10.534 --> 00:56:12.827
Get to them before the agency.

858
00:56:20.043 --> 00:56:23.045
Perfect timing. Lunch is ready.

859
00:56:24.506 --> 00:56:26.257
You must be thirsty.

860
00:56:31.305 --> 00:56:34.182
It's coconut. It's loaded with electrolytes.

861
00:56:37.144 --> 00:56:38.895
Just... Whoa. Okay?

862
00:56:43.400 --> 00:56:44.442
Okay. Just... Whoa.

863
00:56:44.860 --> 00:56:46.319
- (GRUNTS)
- Yeah?

864
00:56:46.820 --> 00:56:48.029
- (GRUNTS)
- Yeah!

865
00:56:49.823 --> 00:56:51.616
Hey. You got skills.

866
00:56:53.869 --> 00:56:55.953
- My dad wanted boys.
- Yeah?

867
00:56:56.538 --> 00:56:59.790
- Let me go.
- You can get out anytime you want.

868
00:56:59.875 --> 00:57:01.375
I'll show you.

869
00:57:02.419 --> 00:57:04.462
Hands like Houdini.

870
00:57:04.546 --> 00:57:06.380
Turn your palms down.

871
00:57:06.715 --> 00:57:08.341
and all at once.

872
00:57:08.842 --> 00:57:12.053
throw your hands to the ground
and your hips back.

873
00:57:15.474 --> 00:57:16.557
Nice.

874
00:57:17.559 --> 00:57:19.018
That was good.

875
00:57:21.730 --> 00:57:23.147
(GRUNTING)

876
00:57:23.649 --> 00:57:25.399
(BOTH LAUGHING)

877
00:57:35.369 --> 00:57:36.744
Who are you?

878
00:57:38.914 --> 00:57:40.081
Really.

879
00:57:47.965 --> 00:57:49.924
(WHOOSHING)

880
00:57:55.097 --> 00:57:56.639
I don't understand.

881
00:57:59.142 --> 00:58:00.351
Follow me.

882
00:58:15.325 --> 00:58:17.910
I don't understand. I came in clean.

883
00:58:19.746 --> 00:58:23.583
My phone is secure. It's secure.
Unless you made a call.

884
00:58:23.667 --> 00:58:26.877
- And you didn't make a call.
- No. I didn't make a call.

885
00:58:26.962 --> 00:58:28.504
I took a call.

886
00:58:30.757 --> 00:58:31.966
You took a call?

887
00:58:32.634 --> 00:58:33.718
It was a quick one.

888
00:58:34.136 --> 00:58:35.303
You...

889
00:58:37.973 --> 00:58:38.973
Come on.

890
00:58:40.058 --> 00:58:41.225
JUNE: I thought we were off the grid.

891
00:58:41.310 --> 00:58:42.518
- and then the phone rang.
- It's okay.

892
00:58:42.603 --> 00:58:44.103
It was my sister and I had to take the call.

893
00:58:44.187 --> 00:58:47.481
- You know? I didn't want her to worry.
- Watch your step.

894
00:58:51.111 --> 00:58:52.361
No. no. no...

895
00:58:52.446 --> 00:58:54.488
I can't get into that.
I just can't get into that thing.

896
00:58:54.781 --> 00:58:56.115
I can't get into that.

897
00:58:57.659 --> 00:58:58.951
- June.
- Roy...

898
00:58:59.119 --> 00:59:02.288
Just. please. knock me out.
Use broton-seven or whatever.

899
00:59:02.956 --> 00:59:04.790
- It's okay.
- You're grabbing my neck.

900
00:59:04.875 --> 00:59:06.459
You asked me not to drug you.

901
00:59:06.752 --> 00:59:08.252
Okay. good.

902
00:59:18.805 --> 00:59:22.683
(GROGGILY) Hands like Houdini. Hands...

903
00:59:24.186 --> 00:59:25.895
(SIGHS SLEEPILY)

904
00:59:28.190 --> 00:59:30.024
(RHYTHMIC CLACKING)

905
00:59:44.039 --> 00:59:45.122
Roy?

906
00:59:48.210 --> 00:59:51.087
(WHOOPING)

907
00:59:52.214 --> 00:59:54.715
- I can't feel my face!
- MILLER: Okay. time.

908
00:59:54.883 --> 00:59:56.092
Okay. Simon...

909
00:59:56.176 --> 00:59:57.802
(TRAIN HORN BLARING)

910
00:59:57.886 --> 00:59:59.512
Roy. the pull on this thing...

911
00:59:59.596 --> 01:00:01.305
- We said 10 minutes.
- The traction on this thing.

912
01:00:01.390 --> 01:00:04.517
- It can pull up to 50.000 metric tons!
- I get it.

913
01:00:04.601 --> 01:00:06.977
(BOTH SPEAKING GERMAN)

914
01:00:07.062 --> 01:00:08.145
It's a diesel hydraulic!

915
01:00:08.313 --> 01:00:10.064
Don't you wanna see your Zephyr?

916
01:00:10.732 --> 01:00:11.816
Yes.

917
01:00:27.416 --> 01:00:29.291
- Excuse me.
- Guten Morgen. miss.

918
01:00:29.376 --> 01:00:30.376
Can you tell me where we are?

919
01:00:30.460 --> 01:00:31.961
Right now. miss? We are in Austria.

920
01:00:32.379 --> 01:00:33.838
Austria. huh?

921
01:00:35.257 --> 01:00:37.466
Would you like some breakfast. miss?

922
01:00:37.551 --> 01:00:39.969
Yeah. that would be great. Thanks.

923
01:00:41.471 --> 01:00:43.848
Okay. I'm gonna have some pancakes.

924
01:00:43.932 --> 01:00:45.182
scrambled eggs...

925
01:00:45.267 --> 01:00:46.475
- Scrambled eggs.
...and...

926
01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:47.852
With a glass of milk.

927
01:00:47.936 --> 01:00:48.978
And a glass of milk.

928
01:00:49.062 --> 01:00:52.106
- Can I get a Harvey Wallbanger. please?
- Certainly. sir.

929
01:00:52.190 --> 01:00:53.566
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

930
01:00:56.611 --> 01:01:00.114
You know. statistically. you're a lot
more likely to die riding on a train

931
01:01:00.198 --> 01:01:02.074
than any other form of transportation.

932
01:01:04.619 --> 01:01:07.246
10.3 times more likely
than dying on a plane.

933
01:01:08.999 --> 01:01:09.999
Simon?

934
01:01:12.377 --> 01:01:13.377
(WHISPERING) Simon Feck?

935
01:01:13.879 --> 01:01:14.920
(HESITANTLY) Yes.

936
01:01:16.465 --> 01:01:19.425
My name is June.
I'm a friend of Roy Miller's.

937
01:01:19.801 --> 01:01:20.885
Oh!

938
01:01:20.969 --> 01:01:22.720
Have you found him yet?
Have you seen him?

939
01:01:22.804 --> 01:01:24.221
- No. not yet.
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)

940
01:01:25.140 --> 01:01:27.433
- Don't you wanna answer that?
- Yeah.

941
01:01:27.976 --> 01:01:28.976
But I can't.

942
01:01:29.060 --> 01:01:30.644
I'm not supposed to.

943
01:01:30.937 --> 01:01:32.062
It might be Roy.

944
01:01:32.147 --> 01:01:36.567
Yeah. but he told me not to answer the
phone. because the signal can be tracked.

945
01:01:36.651 --> 01:01:38.486
That's right. Of course.

946
01:01:45.160 --> 01:01:46.744
(EXHALING)

947
01:01:46.828 --> 01:01:49.580
Did Roy happen to tell you
about the plan here?

948
01:01:49.664 --> 01:01:51.832
- Are we supposed to meet him here. or...
- Um...

949
01:01:52.459 --> 01:01:54.001
What did you say that drink was?

950
01:01:54.085 --> 01:01:56.462
- A Harvey...
- It's a Harvey Wallbanger.

951
01:01:56.671 --> 01:01:58.464
Do you mind just
ordering me one of those?

952
01:01:58.548 --> 01:02:00.341
Because it looks great.

953
01:02:00.425 --> 01:02:02.468
I'll just be right back.
You just stay here for a second.

954
01:02:02.552 --> 01:02:04.261
I'll be right back.

955
01:02:04.679 --> 01:02:08.098
Something is wrong.
It's getting hotter. Roy.

956
01:02:08.183 --> 01:02:09.809
She didn't answer her phone.

957
01:02:09.893 --> 01:02:12.061
- I told her not to. That's...
- We just got here.

958
01:02:12.145 --> 01:02:14.438
- That's good news.
- I'm sure she'll turn up. Roy...

959
01:02:14.523 --> 01:02:17.399
- I left a note posted right there.
- We may have an issue here.

960
01:02:17.484 --> 01:02:20.820
- The temperature...
- She's hungry... She's hungry.

961
01:02:20.904 --> 01:02:23.572
It's getting too hot.
We need to cool it down.

962
01:02:23.657 --> 01:02:25.616
Yeah. she went to get something to eat.

963
01:02:25.700 --> 01:02:27.368
Good. Come on. Simon.

964
01:02:53.186 --> 01:02:55.521
- May I help you?
- Yeah.

965
01:02:55.605 --> 01:02:56.730
I'm feeling a little bit train-sick.

966
01:02:56.815 --> 01:02:58.274
Is it okay if I hang out here for a while?

967
01:02:58.358 --> 01:03:01.026
Of course. I will get you some water.

968
01:03:03.113 --> 01:03:04.113
Here you go.

969
01:03:09.953 --> 01:03:11.537
(SPEAKS GERMAN)

970
01:03:12.205 --> 01:03:13.789
You killed him.

971
01:03:13.874 --> 01:03:15.499
No. you did.

972
01:03:18.044 --> 01:03:19.962
(SCREAMING)

973
01:03:20.046 --> 01:03:24.049
Have you ever watched
The Nature Channel? Hmm?

974
01:03:24.926 --> 01:03:28.679
See. there's this moment
where the cougar catches the fawn.

975
01:03:28.763 --> 01:03:31.682
and the fawn
that has been running for so long.

976
01:03:31.766 --> 01:03:35.477
it just stops and lies down.

977
01:03:36.187 --> 01:03:37.438
(YELPS)

978
01:03:37.856 --> 01:03:40.107
That's a very honest moment.
don't you think?

979
01:03:53.079 --> 01:03:54.788
Where is the battery?

980
01:04:06.301 --> 01:04:07.343
Uh...

981
01:04:08.136 --> 01:04:11.013
I'm sorry. I'm looking for ice.

982
01:04:11.473 --> 01:04:12.473
- Roy.
- Bernhard.

983
01:04:12.557 --> 01:04:13.557
Miller.

984
01:04:13.642 --> 01:04:16.268
- Wrong room.
- It's okay. It's okay.

985
01:04:16.353 --> 01:04:18.270
- You know him?
- Yeah.

986
01:04:18.355 --> 01:04:22.441
He's an assassin. platinum grade.
He's come to collect Simon.

987
01:04:22.525 --> 01:04:23.567
Oh. my God.

988
01:04:23.652 --> 01:04:25.903
- And to kill you.
- That's Simon?

989
01:04:25.987 --> 01:04:28.155
- Yeah. June. Simon. Simon. June.
- Hi.

990
01:04:33.119 --> 01:04:35.663
Jeez! I'm okay. I got this.

991
01:04:44.172 --> 01:04:46.090
Simon. please move.

992
01:04:53.390 --> 01:04:54.390
(CHUCKLING)

993
01:04:59.729 --> 01:05:02.731
You have quite some balls. Fräulein.

994
01:05:04.025 --> 01:05:05.734
Hands like Houdini.

995
01:05:05.819 --> 01:05:07.611
- (GRUNTS)
- (EXCLAIMS)

996
01:05:14.369 --> 01:05:15.828
I'm so sorry.

997
01:05:18.373 --> 01:05:20.708
But you were trying to kill me.

998
01:05:33.221 --> 01:05:34.638
That's disgusting.

999
01:05:42.856 --> 01:05:45.399
Oh. my God. Just die!

1000
01:05:48.695 --> 01:05:49.695
Oh. shit.

1001
01:05:51.364 --> 01:05:54.324
I got to get you guys someplace safe.

1002
01:06:03.668 --> 01:06:06.086
- They're not on the train.
- Oh. really?

1003
01:06:06.171 --> 01:06:07.921
Cameras at the last station show nothing.

1004
01:06:08.006 --> 01:06:10.132
They must have gotten off
between stops.

1005
01:06:10.216 --> 01:06:12.050
Locals haven't found anything.

1006
01:06:42.957 --> 01:06:44.958
Always the classics. Roy.

1007
01:06:48.004 --> 01:06:50.088
Stay here. I'll be back in five.

1008
01:07:23.456 --> 01:07:25.040
Hey. Fitz.

1009
01:07:27.252 --> 01:07:29.378
Hey. Roy.

1010
01:07:29.462 --> 01:07:31.547
Thanks for meeting me.

1011
01:07:31.631 --> 01:07:34.883
Thanks for the white flag.

1012
01:07:34.968 --> 01:07:37.219
You know. when I saw you
through that little circle.

1013
01:07:37.303 --> 01:07:39.054
I saw a man looking for a way out.

1014
01:07:39.138 --> 01:07:44.685
Now. not that the last few days
haven't been absolutely spectacular.

1015
01:07:44.769 --> 01:07:48.063
but I think you know
it's all coming to an end.

1016
01:07:49.482 --> 01:07:52.776
I think you know you're gonna get
your little lady friend killed.

1017
01:07:54.487 --> 01:07:56.572
(JUNE HUMMING)

1018
01:08:00.326 --> 01:08:02.995
The way I see it. you have some options.

1019
01:08:03.079 --> 01:08:05.998
You could sell Simon.
You could sell the battery.

1020
01:08:06.082 --> 01:08:09.585
Shit. you sell both of them.
you'd really set yourself up.

1021
01:08:09.669 --> 01:08:11.461
Or you could turn yourself in.

1022
01:08:12.672 --> 01:08:13.672
I could.

1023
01:08:13.756 --> 01:08:16.967
And that's the safest option for the people
you seem to care so much about.

1024
01:08:17.051 --> 01:08:20.137
Boy genius would be fine.
No one wants to see him hurt.

1025
01:08:20.221 --> 01:08:21.263
And the girl?

1026
01:08:21.347 --> 01:08:23.056
She goes home
having lived through an adventure

1027
01:08:23.141 --> 01:08:26.351
that no one in her little world
will ever believe.

1028
01:08:42.952 --> 01:08:44.119
MILLER: Yes. Uh-huh.

1029
01:08:47.624 --> 01:08:49.499
No. we just got in.

1030
01:08:50.877 --> 01:08:54.046
Well. we're talking now. No. I understand.

1031
01:08:54.255 --> 01:08:56.298
Well. it's good to hear your voice.
too. Naomi.

1032
01:08:56.382 --> 01:08:59.426
I'll meet you at the caprice.
As soon as you can be there.

1033
01:09:08.436 --> 01:09:10.479
It's a beautiful city. huh?

1034
01:09:11.314 --> 01:09:12.397
Yeah.

1035
01:09:13.691 --> 01:09:16.151
Never seen anything quite like it.

1036
01:09:22.075 --> 01:09:23.659
(SOFTLY) Neither have I.

1037
01:09:26.871 --> 01:09:28.538
I got to go out for a bit.

1038
01:09:30.500 --> 01:09:31.708
Okay.

1039
01:09:31.918 --> 01:09:35.045
I was thinking about ordering
some room service.

1040
01:09:36.506 --> 01:09:40.092
And I thought maybe we could
have dinner or something.

1041
01:09:40.259 --> 01:09:42.094
That sounds great.

1042
01:09:43.304 --> 01:09:44.304
9:00?

1043
01:09:46.182 --> 01:09:47.683
9:00 sounds great.

1044
01:09:51.062 --> 01:09:52.104
June?

1045
01:09:53.856 --> 01:09:58.402
Could you do me a favor
and just stick around here? It's better.

1046
01:09:58.820 --> 01:10:02.322
Oh. yeah. of course.
Where else am I gonna go?

1047
01:10:02.490 --> 01:10:04.074
See you in a bit.

1048
01:10:08.705 --> 01:10:11.957
They're not gonna hurt you.
You're too valuable to them.

1049
01:10:12.041 --> 01:10:14.001
Now. just breathe. listen to your music.

1050
01:10:14.085 --> 01:10:16.086
Here. as a matter of fact.
I got that for you.

1051
01:10:17.505 --> 01:10:18.755
I know you like them.

1052
01:10:18.840 --> 01:10:19.965
Cool. thanks.

1053
01:10:20.049 --> 01:10:24.636
Listen. order as much room service
as you like. but don't leave the room.

1054
01:10:24.971 --> 01:10:26.221
Okay.

1055
01:10:27.181 --> 01:10:30.100
- We need to talk about the Zephyr later.
- And we will.

1056
01:11:30.995 --> 01:11:32.329
(WAITER INQUIRING IN GERMAN)

1057
01:11:32.413 --> 01:11:33.538
(ORDERING IN GERMAN)

1058
01:11:54.936 --> 01:11:58.897
I wasn't sure whether you'd come
considering what's happened.

1059
01:12:02.735 --> 01:12:04.319
Life can be funny. isn't it?

1060
01:12:05.905 --> 01:12:07.364
The paths we take.

1061
01:12:08.866 --> 01:12:11.201
Lovers and friends.

1062
01:12:11.285 --> 01:12:12.536
Lost and found.

1063
01:12:14.163 --> 01:12:15.747
You seem different.

1064
01:12:15.832 --> 01:12:16.915
Do I?

1065
01:12:19.877 --> 01:12:22.128
So. who's your companion?

1066
01:12:23.047 --> 01:12:25.298
She's beautiful. The blonde.

1067
01:12:25.883 --> 01:12:27.551
She seems capable.

1068
01:12:28.594 --> 01:12:30.011
I just met her.

1069
01:12:31.097 --> 01:12:32.931
She's a nobody.

1070
01:12:33.099 --> 01:12:36.852
Just someone I picked up along the way.

1071
01:12:37.728 --> 01:12:39.104
That's a shame.

1072
01:12:40.857 --> 01:12:44.192
This is getting boring.
Are we gonna do a deal or not?

1073
01:12:44.652 --> 01:12:46.027
(CHUCKLES)

1074
01:12:46.863 --> 01:12:49.030
Don't speak to me like that.

1075
01:12:51.158 --> 01:12:54.077
I will speak to you any way I please. Tony.

1076
01:12:54.245 --> 01:12:55.912
We both know you're lucky I'm here.

1077
01:12:57.456 --> 01:12:58.456
(SIGHS)

1078
01:12:58.541 --> 01:13:01.501
I have the battery. I'm on a schedule.

1079
01:13:02.003 --> 01:13:04.379
The world is full of bad guys
and people are calling.

1080
01:13:04.881 --> 01:13:07.048
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1081
01:13:09.927 --> 01:13:11.177
I understand.

1082
01:13:12.388 --> 01:13:14.222
What's your price?

1083
01:13:15.892 --> 01:13:17.684
I have a figure in mind.

1084
01:13:17.852 --> 01:13:19.728
What's it worth to you?

1085
01:13:20.187 --> 01:13:23.064
Are you angry about your island. Roy?

1086
01:13:23.232 --> 01:13:25.483
Tick. tick. tick. tick. tick. Tony.

1087
01:13:30.573 --> 01:13:32.908
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

1088
01:13:38.789 --> 01:13:42.876
I'm Isabel George. Director
of Counter Espionage at the CIA.

1089
01:13:43.753 --> 01:13:45.462
I'm sure you are.

1090
01:13:47.381 --> 01:13:49.174
Forgive me. I just...

1091
01:13:51.218 --> 01:13:53.511
I just don't know exactly what to believe.

1092
01:13:55.681 --> 01:13:59.309
Well. that's understandable.
considering that the last five days

1093
01:13:59.393 --> 01:14:02.604
you've been fed a steady diet
of misinformation and fantasy

1094
01:14:02.688 --> 01:14:05.815
by an agent of ours
who's recently gone rogue.

1095
01:14:06.108 --> 01:14:09.861
Well. he said that Fitzgerald was the
one that wanted to steal the battery.

1096
01:14:09.946 --> 01:14:11.488
ISABEL: Well. let's examine the facts.

1097
01:14:11.697 --> 01:14:16.368
Miller told you that he was protecting the
Zephyr from people wanting to misuse it.

1098
01:14:16.535 --> 01:14:19.746
But now he's trying to sell it
to an international arms dealer.

1099
01:14:20.122 --> 01:14:21.790
Antonio Quintana.

1100
01:14:22.208 --> 01:14:24.876
One of Europe's leading
weapons manufacturers.

1101
01:14:25.795 --> 01:14:26.962
Ask yourself. Miss Havens.

1102
01:14:29.799 --> 01:14:33.343
has Roy Miller said anything to you
that's proven to be true?

1103
01:14:35.513 --> 01:14:37.639
JUNE: God. excuse me.
MILLER: No. I'm sorry.

1104
01:14:39.266 --> 01:14:40.934
(AUDIO WARBLING)

1105
01:14:42.311 --> 01:14:45.397
(SLOWED DOWN) Sorry. I was looking at
my phone. I hate it when people do that.

1106
01:14:47.858 --> 01:14:50.110
(EXCLAIMS) Oh. my God. I'm so sorry.

1107
01:14:51.529 --> 01:14:54.572
MILLER: This is getting to be a habit.
JUNE: (CHUCKLING) Yeah. it is.

1108
01:14:55.992 --> 01:15:00.036
ISABEL: He used you as a mule to carry
the battery through security. Miss Havens.

1109
01:15:00.746 --> 01:15:02.622
He's been playing you.

1110
01:15:03.374 --> 01:15:06.292
He's a spy. that's what he does.
He lies for a living.

1111
01:15:06.377 --> 01:15:09.587
Any love. empathy.
we train that right out of them.

1112
01:15:09.755 --> 01:15:11.256
What did you imagine?

1113
01:15:11.424 --> 01:15:14.676
The two of you would move
into a condo together. get a dog?

1114
01:15:14.844 --> 01:15:17.887
You can't have a life with him.
That's fantasy.

1115
01:15:18.556 --> 01:15:20.181
But you can have yours back.

1116
01:15:20.516 --> 01:15:21.850
She's been gone eight minutes.

1117
01:15:22.018 --> 01:15:25.020
We need you to get back to the hotel
before Miller.

1118
01:15:27.356 --> 01:15:30.358
- What am I supposed to do?
- FITZGERALD: All right. then.

1119
01:15:32.862 --> 01:15:34.612
This pen is a transmitter.

1120
01:15:35.114 --> 01:15:37.699
Once you have confirmation
that Miller has not hidden the Zephyr.

1121
01:15:37.783 --> 01:15:40.910
that it's somewhere nearby.
or on his person.

1122
01:15:41.704 --> 01:15:45.206
you can confirm this
by simply clicking the top button.

1123
01:15:46.876 --> 01:15:48.418
(DOOR OPENING)

1124
01:15:54.592 --> 01:15:56.384
I'm sorry I'm late.

1125
01:15:57.720 --> 01:15:59.429
Everything go okay?

1126
01:16:02.266 --> 01:16:03.683
Well enough.

1127
01:16:08.481 --> 01:16:09.647
It's getting hotter.

1128
01:16:12.068 --> 01:16:13.443
(SIZZLING)

1129
01:16:20.576 --> 01:16:22.452
So. did you get your price?

1130
01:16:26.957 --> 01:16:28.875
I followed you tonight.

1131
01:16:33.589 --> 01:16:35.256
You have nothing to say?

1132
01:16:36.383 --> 01:16:38.802
Here's to Wichita

1133
01:16:41.597 --> 01:16:42.806
where we first...

1134
01:16:43.641 --> 01:16:45.558
Bumped into each other.

1135
01:16:49.105 --> 01:16:51.106
Do you think that was fate. Roy?

1136
01:16:52.900 --> 01:16:54.859
I don't believe in fate.

1137
01:16:55.820 --> 01:16:57.695
But I believe in luck.

1138
01:17:00.241 --> 01:17:02.450
I don't know what to believe.

1139
01:17:11.877 --> 01:17:13.086
Huh.

1140
01:17:14.296 --> 01:17:17.048
That hurt more than I thought it would.

1141
01:17:21.762 --> 01:17:23.304
I'm going home.

1142
01:17:33.983 --> 01:17:38.820
They promised that if you turned
yourself in. they'd protect you.

1143
01:17:41.115 --> 01:17:42.907
I love your optimism.

1144
01:17:44.243 --> 01:17:45.326
Never lose it.

1145
01:17:48.164 --> 01:17:49.956
(MEN SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1146
01:17:52.793 --> 01:17:54.169
FITZGERALD: Get her out of here.

1147
01:18:10.394 --> 01:18:12.145
MAN: He's not here. sir.

1148
01:18:12.646 --> 01:18:15.190
Did they tell you you're going home?

1149
01:18:15.566 --> 01:18:17.901
You've seen the inside
of the honeycomb. June!

1150
01:18:18.527 --> 01:18:19.819
You can't go home.

1151
01:18:20.070 --> 01:18:22.155
OFFICER ON RADIO:
The suspect is on the roof.

1152
01:18:22.239 --> 01:18:24.782
- (HELICOPTER WHIRRING)
- (WHISTLE BLOWING)

1153
01:18:25.993 --> 01:18:27.035
Oh. shit.

1154
01:18:30.664 --> 01:18:32.415
(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1155
01:18:41.467 --> 01:18:44.052
(MAN SPEAKING GERMAN
ON LOUDSPEAKER)

1156
01:18:45.846 --> 01:18:47.430
Director George!

1157
01:18:47.932 --> 01:18:49.641
Get her in the car.

1158
01:19:40.150 --> 01:19:41.776
FITZGERALD: He's heading toward the river.

1159
01:19:42.611 --> 01:19:44.654
(BOTH SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1160
01:19:55.791 --> 01:19:57.959
Stand down! He has the battery!

1161
01:20:06.677 --> 01:20:08.553
Hey! Hey! Hold it!

1162
01:20:08.721 --> 01:20:09.804
Hold your fire!

1163
01:20:09.972 --> 01:20:11.055
Stand down!

1164
01:20:11.223 --> 01:20:12.223
He has the battery!

1165
01:20:17.479 --> 01:20:18.563
(SPLASHING)

1166
01:20:18.647 --> 01:20:19.856
(GASPS)

1167
01:20:21.650 --> 01:20:23.901
(POLICEMEN SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

1168
01:20:31.160 --> 01:20:32.827
Did you secure the kid?

1169
01:20:33.662 --> 01:20:34.662
Yeah.

1170
01:20:43.839 --> 01:20:45.006
Did they find Roy?

1171
01:20:45.341 --> 01:20:47.967
We'll find the body. We have to.

1172
01:20:48.302 --> 01:20:50.345
He went down with the Zephyr.

1173
01:21:21.043 --> 01:21:22.835
(GUESTS APPLAUDING)

1174
01:21:25.339 --> 01:21:27.006
(APRIL GIGGLING)

1175
01:21:28.342 --> 01:21:30.301
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

1176
01:21:35.182 --> 01:21:38.935
APRIL: Ben and I would like
to thank all of you for coming.

1177
01:21:39.019 --> 01:21:44.774
And I'd like to say a special thanks
to my sister. June.

1178
01:21:44.858 --> 01:21:48.361
who many of you will recognize
from America's Most Wanted.

1179
01:21:48.821 --> 01:21:50.655
(GUESTS LAUGHING)

1180
01:21:53.450 --> 01:21:55.243
Thank you.

1181
01:21:55.327 --> 01:22:00.164
Not just for helping me with tonight.
but for helping me every night.

1182
01:22:02.835 --> 01:22:04.293
(CHUCKLES)

1183
01:22:04.378 --> 01:22:09.715
I know that it probably wasn't always
the life you envisioned.

1184
01:22:11.385 --> 01:22:15.346
You gave up so much
so that I could lead the life that I wanted.

1185
01:22:21.895 --> 01:22:23.646
A toast.

1186
01:22:23.730 --> 01:22:29.277
Here's to a year
when June comes before April.

1187
01:22:29.778 --> 01:22:32.238
(GUESTS APPLAUDING)

1188
01:22:38.287 --> 01:22:39.454
(SOFTLY) Thank you.

1189
01:22:57.389 --> 01:22:59.765
(MUSIC BLARING OVER HEADPHONES)

1190
01:23:03.353 --> 01:23:04.645
Fitz?

1191
01:23:04.730 --> 01:23:08.649
Fitz. I think we just made a wrong turn.
Ramstein is that way. west.

1192
01:23:08.734 --> 01:23:10.485
I think we're going south.

1193
01:23:10.652 --> 01:23:12.487
You know what? You're right.

1194
01:23:20.829 --> 01:23:22.788
Tell him we're back on track.

1195
01:23:22.956 --> 01:23:26.083
I don't have the battery.
but no one's gonna get it now.

1196
01:23:26.251 --> 01:23:28.085
Yeah. I've got the next best thing.

1197
01:23:28.295 --> 01:23:30.755
I'll see you in Spain in two days.

1198
01:23:34.676 --> 01:23:36.302
(METAL CLANKING)

1199
01:23:41.350 --> 01:23:42.683
Hey. Wilmer.

1200
01:23:44.061 --> 01:23:45.895
- How was the party?
- It was nice.

1201
01:23:46.313 --> 01:23:48.689
- I see the goat is still out there.
- Yeah.

1202
01:23:48.857 --> 01:23:50.566
I thought it was a wedding present.

1203
01:23:50.734 --> 01:23:52.568
It was. but.

1204
01:23:54.613 --> 01:23:57.156
I think I wanted her to want it
more than she wanted it.

1205
01:23:58.367 --> 01:23:59.534
Okay.

1206
01:24:00.619 --> 01:24:02.328
I think I'm gonna give her the house.

1207
01:24:03.413 --> 01:24:04.539
Wow.

1208
01:24:05.082 --> 01:24:06.332
I mean.

1209
01:24:07.709 --> 01:24:09.961
she and Ben need a place of their own.

1210
01:24:10.796 --> 01:24:12.004
That's nice.

1211
01:24:12.923 --> 01:24:16.676
DJ ON RADIO: Boston's classic
rock station. Here are the Kingsmen.

1212
01:24:16.843 --> 01:24:18.010
This just come in?

1213
01:24:18.178 --> 01:24:20.930
G-body Grand Prix.
Longest hood in history.

1214
01:24:21.848 --> 01:24:23.599
Gonna be a real beaut.

1215
01:24:23.684 --> 01:24:24.934
(LOUIE LOUIE PLAYING ON RADIO)

1216
01:24:25.018 --> 01:24:26.644
Oh. no

1217
01:24:26.728 --> 01:24:28.854
Me gotta go

1218
01:24:32.359 --> 01:24:35.945
(MUTTERING TO HERSELF)
Ru-pa... Fee-pa... No. it's...

1219
01:24:36.530 --> 01:24:39.407
5826 Amapola.

1220
01:24:42.035 --> 01:24:44.036
That's like an hour from here.

1221
01:24:44.871 --> 01:24:46.664
Maybe it's a safe-house.

1222
01:24:46.748 --> 01:24:48.791
(POWERFUL ENGINE STARTING)

1223
01:24:54.590 --> 01:24:56.299
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1224
01:25:21.700 --> 01:25:23.075
Here we go.

1225
01:25:24.703 --> 01:25:26.370
(HORNS BLARING)

1226
01:26:14.711 --> 01:26:15.711
(GASPS)

1227
01:26:16.296 --> 01:26:17.380
(EXCLAIMS) Shit!

1228
01:26:18.965 --> 01:26:20.257
(SHOTGUN COCKING)

1229
01:26:20.342 --> 01:26:23.052
Who's out there?
I'm not afraid to use this.

1230
01:26:23.136 --> 01:26:24.720
MOLLY: Oh. Frank. look at her!

1231
01:26:24.971 --> 01:26:27.348
I want to know what she's doing
on my lawn in the middle of the night.

1232
01:26:27.516 --> 01:26:29.141
I... I have the pistons you ordered.

1233
01:26:29.309 --> 01:26:30.601
Pistons?

1234
01:26:30.769 --> 01:26:32.311
For the '67 Grand Prix.

1235
01:26:32.604 --> 01:26:34.230
Molly. I didn't...

1236
01:26:34.815 --> 01:26:37.274
You are all wet. Please. come inside.

1237
01:26:38.193 --> 01:26:40.152
(COMMENTATOR CHATTERING)

1238
01:26:44.950 --> 01:26:47.535
That Pontiac you have out there. Frank.
is a real classic.

1239
01:26:47.619 --> 01:26:48.661
FRANK: Mmm-hmm.

1240
01:26:49.162 --> 01:26:51.831
I really love pre-'70s Grand Prixs.

1241
01:26:51.915 --> 01:26:53.040
FRANK: Mmm-hmm.

1242
01:26:53.125 --> 01:26:55.251
So. you two lived here long?

1243
01:26:55.836 --> 01:26:59.422
This old place?
It's been our home for 40 years.

1244
01:27:00.048 --> 01:27:02.341
Sit down. honey. Have a cookie.

1245
01:27:03.385 --> 01:27:06.554
Frank thinks we should move.
but you know what? I am comfortable.

1246
01:27:06.763 --> 01:27:10.182
And we can afford to stay.
thanks to Publishers Clearing House.

1247
01:27:13.311 --> 01:27:14.854
You won Publishers Clearing House?

1248
01:27:14.938 --> 01:27:18.357
- Twice.
- Plus. we won two lotto quick picks

1249
01:27:18.442 --> 01:27:20.943
- Frank doesn't even remember buying.
- Because I didn't buy them.

1250
01:27:21.027 --> 01:27:24.113
Oh. yeah. like you didn't order pistons
off the Internet.

1251
01:27:24.531 --> 01:27:28.200
You don't know what you're typing
into that computer. Frank.

1252
01:27:28.493 --> 01:27:31.620
Another couple of minutes
on your clothes. honey.

1253
01:27:33.123 --> 01:27:34.123
(SOFTLY) So.

1254
01:27:36.460 --> 01:27:37.835
Roy Miller.

1255
01:27:39.546 --> 01:27:41.839
This was one of his safe-houses.
wasn't it?

1256
01:27:42.716 --> 01:27:44.383
(TURNS OFF TV)

1257
01:27:45.510 --> 01:27:46.886
What in the hell are you talking about?

1258
01:27:49.222 --> 01:27:50.556
Honey. what's this all about?

1259
01:27:52.350 --> 01:27:56.437
(STAMMERING) I'm sorry.
I just thought. maybe...

1260
01:27:56.897 --> 01:27:58.731
I must've had this all wrong.

1261
01:27:59.065 --> 01:28:03.402
I was just looking for some information
about my friend. Roy.

1262
01:28:05.113 --> 01:28:08.574
If you'd like to change.
there's a powder room right there.

1263
01:28:19.711 --> 01:28:21.587
That's our son. Matthew.

1264
01:28:21.755 --> 01:28:24.757
We lost him in Kuwait.
There was a chopper crash.

1265
01:28:24.925 --> 01:28:28.093
He saved the lives
of two of his crewmen. and...

1266
01:28:29.471 --> 01:28:31.138
He just always took care of everyone.

1267
01:28:31.306 --> 01:28:32.848
He was an Eagle Scout.

1268
01:28:32.933 --> 01:28:36.268
This was taken the day
he got that swimming badge.

1269
01:28:36.436 --> 01:28:39.730
He could swim clear across Lake Sunapee

1270
01:28:39.898 --> 01:28:41.982
with practically one breath.

1271
01:28:44.319 --> 01:28:45.819
I just...

1272
01:28:46.947 --> 01:28:49.323
I've been terribly rude.

1273
01:28:49.950 --> 01:28:51.742
I'm June Havens.

1274
01:28:52.077 --> 01:28:53.536
Molly Knight.

1275
01:28:54.454 --> 01:28:57.206
This is June Havens. and I'm leaving
a message on my own machine

1276
01:28:57.290 --> 01:28:59.959
for whoever is listening to this phone call.

1277
01:29:00.252 --> 01:29:01.919
I have the Zephyr.

1278
01:29:02.337 --> 01:29:05.130
I have the Zephyr.
and I'm ready to make a deal.

1279
01:29:06.466 --> 01:29:10.970
I'm sitting on Route 28.
right outside New Hampshire.

1280
01:29:11.638 --> 01:29:13.305
And if you want the Zephyr.

1281
01:29:13.557 --> 01:29:15.558
you better come and get it.

1282
01:29:18.436 --> 01:29:19.812
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1283
01:29:24.943 --> 01:29:26.610
(ENGINE STARTING)

1284
01:29:39.082 --> 01:29:41.125
(MEN EXCLAIMING IN SPANISH)

1285
01:29:51.177 --> 01:29:52.177
Hey. fellas.

1286
01:29:57.809 --> 01:29:58.976
So.

1287
01:29:59.519 --> 01:30:01.270
you want the Zephyr?

1288
01:30:01.938 --> 01:30:04.356
I got the Zephyr. It's right here.

1289
01:30:04.524 --> 01:30:05.899
Come and get it.

1290
01:30:06.359 --> 01:30:07.901
(BELL TOLLING)

1291
01:30:13.199 --> 01:30:15.618
- (MARCHING BAND PLAYING)
- (PEOPLE CHEERING)

1292
01:30:15.702 --> 01:30:17.369
(HONKING)

1293
01:30:23.251 --> 01:30:26.337
Come on. Let's go!

1294
01:30:26.671 --> 01:30:28.213
JUNE: Ouch!
ANTONIO: Welcome to España.

1295
01:30:35.096 --> 01:30:36.889
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1296
01:30:39.434 --> 01:30:42.061
Today is the festival of San Fermin.

1297
01:30:44.898 --> 01:30:47.775
Have you ever seen a bullfight.
Miss Havens?

1298
01:30:53.990 --> 01:30:55.741
My name is Antonio Quintana.

1299
01:30:56.785 --> 01:30:58.494
(LAUGHING) I know who you are.

1300
01:31:00.747 --> 01:31:02.414
What did he give me?

1301
01:31:03.249 --> 01:31:05.501
It's something we're developing
at my company.

1302
01:31:05.585 --> 01:31:07.419
A new kind of truth serum.

1303
01:31:07.754 --> 01:31:08.921
Really?

1304
01:31:09.464 --> 01:31:11.048
(EXHALES GIDDILY)

1305
01:31:11.132 --> 01:31:13.759
I have a few questions for you
about the battery.

1306
01:31:13.843 --> 01:31:17.221
since we both know
what you gave to my men was a joke.

1307
01:31:17.722 --> 01:31:18.764
Wow.

1308
01:31:18.932 --> 01:31:19.932
(CHUCKLES)

1309
01:31:21.267 --> 01:31:23.102
I don't like you very much.

1310
01:31:23.603 --> 01:31:24.853
(CHUCKLING)

1311
01:31:25.355 --> 01:31:26.438
The truth!

1312
01:31:26.898 --> 01:31:28.440
(GIGGLING)

1313
01:31:29.067 --> 01:31:30.150
Good!

1314
01:31:30.527 --> 01:31:31.568
(SPEAKS SOFTLY IN SPANISH)

1315
01:31:31.653 --> 01:31:32.736
JUNE: Wow.

1316
01:31:32.821 --> 01:31:35.489
You know. I really like Miller. though.

1317
01:31:35.657 --> 01:31:38.701
'Cause. you know. I was totally wrong
about him in Salzburg.

1318
01:31:38.868 --> 01:31:41.412
He wanted me to hear that phone call
so that I would follow him.

1319
01:31:41.496 --> 01:31:43.997
I'd turn him in.
and then he could get me home safely.

1320
01:31:44.082 --> 01:31:45.416
He was trying to protect me.

1321
01:31:45.500 --> 01:31:46.709
Shut up.

1322
01:31:47.001 --> 01:31:51.130
It's crazy that I could feel
so powerful and capable around him...

1323
01:31:51.214 --> 01:31:54.299
- Shut up.
...and yet he takes care of me.

1324
01:31:54.467 --> 01:31:57.302
Shut up! Where is the battery?
Where is it?

1325
01:31:58.805 --> 01:32:01.640
I bet you've never made a girl
an omelette. have you. Antonio?

1326
01:32:01.933 --> 01:32:03.475
(LAUGHING)

1327
01:32:04.978 --> 01:32:06.186
Don't test me. June.

1328
01:32:06.354 --> 01:32:08.772
Or got her to her sister's wedding
on time.

1329
01:32:08.857 --> 01:32:10.899
It's really the little things. honestly.

1330
01:32:11.067 --> 01:32:13.110
- But they count so much.
- Enough!

1331
01:32:13.570 --> 01:32:14.653
(CHUCKLING) Okay!

1332
01:32:14.904 --> 01:32:17.406
Miller is dead!
Roy Miller is dead. he's out.

1333
01:32:17.490 --> 01:32:18.741
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1334
01:32:18.825 --> 01:32:19.950
No.

1335
01:32:20.201 --> 01:32:23.412
No. he's not. He can hold his breath
for a really long time.

1336
01:32:23.496 --> 01:32:24.872
(SPEAKING EMPHATICALLY IN SPANISH)

1337
01:32:24.956 --> 01:32:26.039
He is dead!

1338
01:33:03.203 --> 01:33:07.748
I'm not gonna ask you again. But if
you don't tell me what I need to know.

1339
01:33:09.125 --> 01:33:11.335
- (WHISPERING) you're gonna die!
- I don't know where the battery is.

1340
01:33:11.419 --> 01:33:13.253
Then why did you tell everyone
you had it? Why?

1341
01:33:13.338 --> 01:33:15.297
Because I was trying to find Roy.

1342
01:33:15.381 --> 01:33:18.217
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1343
01:33:18.301 --> 01:33:23.222
Well. Antonio. whenever there's bad guys
like you around. Roy's not too far away.

1344
01:33:25.058 --> 01:33:26.558
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1345
01:33:27.393 --> 01:33:28.977
You're gonna die.

1346
01:33:40.323 --> 01:33:41.573
Finally!

1347
01:33:43.034 --> 01:33:45.494
Nice to meet you. John.

1348
01:33:45.662 --> 01:33:46.745
Antonio.

1349
01:33:47.205 --> 01:33:48.831
Too bad you couldn't get the battery.

1350
01:33:51.376 --> 01:33:52.876
Where is the boy?

1351
01:33:55.755 --> 01:33:58.215
You didn't think
I'd just bring the package. did you?

1352
01:34:00.802 --> 01:34:03.428
Why don't you follow me down
to the river and bring the money?

1353
01:34:03.513 --> 01:34:04.596
Okay.

1354
01:34:19.571 --> 01:34:21.113
(BEEPING)

1355
01:34:24.659 --> 01:34:26.243
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1356
01:34:37.881 --> 01:34:41.550
JUNE: Is this thatching in here? Because
I've never seen anything like that before.

1357
01:34:41.634 --> 01:34:45.345
We have really old architecture
in Boston. but nothing like this.

1358
01:34:45.430 --> 01:34:47.681
You're really lucky. because this place is...

1359
01:34:48.099 --> 01:34:51.310
Let me tell you.
You're really lucky. it's beautiful here.

1360
01:34:51.895 --> 01:34:53.103
My thoughts are so clear.

1361
01:34:53.187 --> 01:34:54.313
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1362
01:34:54.647 --> 01:34:57.524
Is this all weapons money.
or is this family money?

1363
01:34:59.193 --> 01:35:01.987
Gardens! He likes gardens. huh?

1364
01:35:02.196 --> 01:35:04.156
Do you guys ever do any gardening?

1365
01:35:04.240 --> 01:35:07.075
It's really relaxing.
It's amazing how much you can just...

1366
01:35:07.160 --> 01:35:10.746
This really is a happy place.
Look at these trumpet flowers. They...

1367
01:35:10.830 --> 01:35:12.581
Okay. Eduardo.
you don't have to pull me around.

1368
01:35:12.665 --> 01:35:14.917
You can just tell me
where you want me to go. okay?

1369
01:35:15.001 --> 01:35:16.126
This way. blondie.

1370
01:35:16.210 --> 01:35:18.337
- See? Now we're communicating.
- Uh-huh.

1371
01:35:19.255 --> 01:35:20.631
I bet you're taking me
someplace safe and secure.

1372
01:35:20.715 --> 01:35:21.757
(MAN GRUNTS IN SURPRISE)

1373
01:35:21.841 --> 01:35:23.884
Someplace special.
Antonio's special place.

1374
01:35:24.010 --> 01:35:25.928
Antonio has a special place?
That's so nice.

1375
01:35:26.012 --> 01:35:27.304
Everyone should have a special place.

1376
01:35:27.388 --> 01:35:29.139
(SPEAKING GRUFFLY IN SPANISH)

1377
01:35:37.023 --> 01:35:39.775
- Luis?
- Is there a problem. Eduardo?

1378
01:35:40.318 --> 01:35:41.318
(BARKS ORDER IN SPANISH)

1379
01:35:46.324 --> 01:35:49.326
- Hi. Roy.
- Hi. June. You're supposed to be home.

1380
01:35:49.410 --> 01:35:51.620
- You're supposed to be dead.
- I can explain.

1381
01:35:51.704 --> 01:35:53.497
- You don't have to.
- I came here to get Simon.

1382
01:35:53.581 --> 01:35:56.416
- I just. you know. caught up with him.
- That's cool.

1383
01:36:00.546 --> 01:36:01.546
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1384
01:36:01.631 --> 01:36:03.799
His name is Eduardo. Eduardo.

1385
01:36:03.883 --> 01:36:06.551
(BOTH SPEAKING SPANISH)

1386
01:36:06.636 --> 01:36:08.345
I need you to listen.
because when you wake up.

1387
01:36:08.429 --> 01:36:10.389
you're gonna call your boss
and you're gonna tell him

1388
01:36:10.473 --> 01:36:13.517
that Roy Miller. that's me.
has the battery and escaped with the girl.

1389
01:36:13.601 --> 01:36:15.185
- You have the battery?
- Yeah.

1390
01:36:15.269 --> 01:36:17.896
- Oh.
- You tell him I'm coming for him.

1391
01:36:18.106 --> 01:36:19.147
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1392
01:36:19.232 --> 01:36:20.232
- Yes.
- Okay.

1393
01:36:21.275 --> 01:36:22.317
Let's go.

1394
01:36:22.860 --> 01:36:25.737
I'm worried about Simon.
I haven't seen him.

1395
01:36:25.989 --> 01:36:27.906
My tracker has been spotty.

1396
01:36:27.991 --> 01:36:30.784
(WHISPERING BREATHLESSLY) Life with
you is so exciting. You excite me. Miller.

1397
01:36:30.868 --> 01:36:32.035
I took too long to get here.

1398
01:36:32.120 --> 01:36:33.412
- 7:00.
- What?

1399
01:36:33.496 --> 01:36:34.705
7:00.

1400
01:36:35.915 --> 01:36:36.915
(GROANING)

1401
01:36:38.001 --> 01:36:40.168
(MAN SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

1402
01:36:43.589 --> 01:36:45.924
I think I feel like having sex.

1403
01:36:46.009 --> 01:36:47.342
(PANTING)

1404
01:36:47.927 --> 01:36:49.594
I think we'd have really great sex.

1405
01:36:51.222 --> 01:36:52.222
Did they give you something?

1406
01:36:52.849 --> 01:36:53.932
Uh-huh.

1407
01:36:54.100 --> 01:36:55.434
You should hydrate.

1408
01:36:56.686 --> 01:36:57.728
Roy?

1409
01:37:03.943 --> 01:37:05.027
Roy.

1410
01:37:10.199 --> 01:37:11.199
(HISSING) Roy?

1411
01:37:11.617 --> 01:37:12.743
(WHISPERING) June.

1412
01:37:14.203 --> 01:37:16.747
(GUNS FIRING)

1413
01:37:18.833 --> 01:37:19.833
June?

1414
01:37:21.461 --> 01:37:23.295
You don't seem
very happy to see me. Roy.

1415
01:37:25.923 --> 01:37:26.965
What?

1416
01:37:27.717 --> 01:37:28.967
Not really.

1417
01:37:48.488 --> 01:37:49.821
(WHISPERING) I am happy.

1418
01:37:50.239 --> 01:37:52.240
- (WEAPONS FIRING)
- (MEN SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

1419
01:37:52.325 --> 01:37:54.576
(MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING)

1420
01:37:59.040 --> 01:38:01.041
- So the red dot is us?
- No. we're yellow.

1421
01:38:01.125 --> 01:38:02.250
The red dot is Simon.

1422
01:38:03.044 --> 01:38:05.712
ANTONIO: Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

1423
01:38:21.229 --> 01:38:22.646
- Air time.
- (ALARMED) Air time?

1424
01:38:39.664 --> 01:38:40.914
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)
- (ANSWERS IN SPANISH)

1425
01:38:42.333 --> 01:38:45.293
He says his name is Roy Miller.
He says he has the battery.

1426
01:38:45.628 --> 01:38:48.046
(SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

1427
01:38:49.340 --> 01:38:50.340
(EXCLAIMS IN SPANISH)

1428
01:38:51.467 --> 01:38:52.551
Miller is here.

1429
01:38:55.888 --> 01:38:59.057
There he is!

1430
01:39:00.518 --> 01:39:02.352
This way. Follow me!

1431
01:39:06.774 --> 01:39:08.525
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

1432
01:39:14.407 --> 01:39:15.490
Bulls?

1433
01:39:27.086 --> 01:39:28.336
(BULLET WHINING)

1434
01:39:35.678 --> 01:39:37.721
- There's Fitz!
- I see him.

1435
01:39:51.027 --> 01:39:52.027
Oh. my God.

1436
01:39:54.947 --> 01:39:57.032
(BIKE ENGINE REVVING)

1437
01:39:57.575 --> 01:39:58.700
(SPEAKS SPANISH)

1438
01:40:14.050 --> 01:40:16.009
Roy. Roy. Roy. Roy. Roy!

1439
01:40:21.015 --> 01:40:22.724
(JUNE WHIMPERING)

1440
01:40:24.435 --> 01:40:26.269
(SPEAKS SPANISH)

1441
01:40:30.399 --> 01:40:31.399
Up there.

1442
01:40:40.952 --> 01:40:43.954
- Which way?
- I don't know. We lost the signal.

1443
01:40:48.376 --> 01:40:50.085
(CROWD CHEERING)

1444
01:41:09.188 --> 01:41:10.939
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1445
01:41:14.819 --> 01:41:16.194
(SCREAMING)

1446
01:41:39.510 --> 01:41:41.344
MILLER: Take the guns.
JUNE: Okay.

1447
01:41:42.888 --> 01:41:44.431
Here.

1448
01:41:44.849 --> 01:41:47.058
- What next?
- Let them have it.

1449
01:41:55.860 --> 01:41:57.027
Mag.

1450
01:42:16.964 --> 01:42:18.006
(SCREAMING)

1451
01:42:21.052 --> 01:42:23.845
June Havens. you've got skills.

1452
01:42:26.223 --> 01:42:27.474
Let's go!

1453
01:42:40.821 --> 01:42:41.863
Go.

1454
01:42:41.989 --> 01:42:43.740
(CAR ALARM WAILING)

1455
01:42:55.086 --> 01:42:56.669
(CARS HONKING)

1456
01:43:06.222 --> 01:43:07.764
- See you down there.
- Are you sure?

1457
01:43:07.848 --> 01:43:09.015
No.

1458
01:43:13.854 --> 01:43:15.021
Sorry.

1459
01:43:18.359 --> 01:43:19.901
- Get up.
- Okay.

1460
01:43:29.537 --> 01:43:30.954
Freeze right there. Roy!

1461
01:43:31.038 --> 01:43:32.080
Hey. Simon.

1462
01:43:32.164 --> 01:43:33.581
Get down on your knees. now!

1463
01:43:33.666 --> 01:43:35.208
- Roy!
- Now! Now!

1464
01:43:35.709 --> 01:43:37.043
Put them in the water. In the water.

1465
01:43:38.212 --> 01:43:39.587
I just want the kid. Fitz.

1466
01:43:41.298 --> 01:43:42.340
FITZGERALD: Okay.

1467
01:43:42.425 --> 01:43:45.093
Well. I hope you brought what I want.
otherwise I'm gonna have to kill him.

1468
01:43:45.177 --> 01:43:47.220
And I swear to you. I'll do it.

1469
01:43:47.513 --> 01:43:50.390
I believe you. Just like Wichita.

1470
01:43:50.724 --> 01:43:52.725
- I understand.
- Okay.

1471
01:43:52.852 --> 01:43:54.227
I'm just gonna get the battery.

1472
01:43:54.478 --> 01:43:56.146
- It's right here.
- SIMON: Don't give it to him. Roy.

1473
01:43:56.230 --> 01:43:57.689
Please don't give it to him. No. no.

1474
01:43:57.773 --> 01:43:58.982
Roy. Roy. please don't give it to him.

1475
01:44:00.317 --> 01:44:01.651
FITZGERALD: Put it on the deck.

1476
01:44:01.735 --> 01:44:03.903
- Roy. Roy. please don't give it to him!
- FITZGERALD: Easy. easy.

1477
01:44:03.988 --> 01:44:05.113
Simon. it's okay.

1478
01:44:05.197 --> 01:44:06.364
Roy. don't give it to him!

1479
01:44:06.449 --> 01:44:09.242
- Shut it! Stop it! Shut it!
- Roy! Whoa! Whoa!

1480
01:44:16.167 --> 01:44:18.376
Okay. Okay. I'll make another one.

1481
01:44:18.461 --> 01:44:19.711
- You don't understand.
- Simon. don't talk.

1482
01:44:19.795 --> 01:44:22.922
- SIMON: I'll just make another one.
- Make another one?

1483
01:44:26.802 --> 01:44:27.844
(GUNSHOT)

1484
01:44:27.928 --> 01:44:29.596
(GULLS SQUAWKING)

1485
01:44:30.931 --> 01:44:32.807
(BOAT ENGINE DRONING)

1486
01:44:40.441 --> 01:44:41.900
Am I dying?

1487
01:44:43.152 --> 01:44:44.527
No. you fainted.

1488
01:44:45.946 --> 01:44:48.156
- I'm sorry.
- No. that's okay.

1489
01:44:48.240 --> 01:44:50.325
No. no. I've been trying to tell you...

1490
01:44:51.285 --> 01:44:52.827
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1491
01:44:55.122 --> 01:44:56.623
Why is it hot?

1492
01:44:57.124 --> 01:44:59.334
Because it's filled with power.

1493
01:44:59.627 --> 01:45:02.378
The battery... I messed up.
It's deteriorating.

1494
01:45:02.463 --> 01:45:04.380
I know. It's unstable.

1495
01:45:04.840 --> 01:45:05.840
Hmm.

1496
01:45:16.018 --> 01:45:19.604
You're a smart guy. Simon.
I know you'll figure it out.

1497
01:45:22.316 --> 01:45:23.650
(SIMON GROANING)

1498
01:45:24.443 --> 01:45:25.485
Oh. my glasses. Thank you.

1499
01:45:27.154 --> 01:45:28.196
Roy.

1500
01:45:28.280 --> 01:45:29.656
you're shot.

1501
01:45:31.951 --> 01:45:33.243
Get help.

1502
01:45:42.169 --> 01:45:43.211
(SOFTLY) Roy.

1503
01:45:44.755 --> 01:45:46.714
(SIREN APPROACHING)

1504
01:45:48.634 --> 01:45:50.843
(WEAKLY) You're beautiful. June Havens.

1505
01:45:57.142 --> 01:45:58.851
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

1506
01:46:03.023 --> 01:46:05.984
(DISTANTLY) Stay with me.
Roy. look at me.

1507
01:46:07.194 --> 01:46:08.361
Stay with me.

1508
01:46:11.740 --> 01:46:15.034
We're here now. Miller.
We got you. We got you.

1509
01:46:17.746 --> 01:46:19.289
DOCTOR: Charge at 360.
MILLER: June.

1510
01:46:19.373 --> 01:46:20.540
DOCTOR: Clear!

1511
01:46:28.299 --> 01:46:30.383
(MONITORS BEEPING STEADILY)

1512
01:46:31.844 --> 01:46:33.678
(LOUIE LOUIE RINGTONE PLAYING)

1513
01:46:33.762 --> 01:46:35.638
Oh. no

1514
01:46:35.723 --> 01:46:37.599
Me gotta go

1515
01:46:37.683 --> 01:46:39.434
Aye-yi-yi-yi. I said

1516
01:46:39.518 --> 01:46:40.852
Louie Louie...

1517
01:46:40.936 --> 01:46:43.021
- (GRUNTS)
- (RINGTONE STOPS)

1518
01:46:45.524 --> 01:46:48.610
It's been a spectacular
couple of weeks. Miller.

1519
01:46:51.405 --> 01:46:53.573
It's good to see you. Isabel.

1520
01:46:56.535 --> 01:46:57.535
Hi. guys.

1521
01:46:58.996 --> 01:47:00.872
You cleaned house. Roy.

1522
01:47:02.458 --> 01:47:04.667
I have to thank you for that.

1523
01:47:06.045 --> 01:47:07.920
(SIGHING) I trusted the wrong man.

1524
01:47:08.589 --> 01:47:09.922
It happens.

1525
01:47:12.593 --> 01:47:15.845
Simon's happy. He's got a new lab.

1526
01:47:17.848 --> 01:47:18.848
Where is June?

1527
01:47:19.975 --> 01:47:21.601
I sent her home.

1528
01:47:24.772 --> 01:47:26.105
She gets it.

1529
01:47:27.900 --> 01:47:30.485
She knows you two lead different lives
and she's moving on.

1530
01:47:30.944 --> 01:47:32.445
As should you.

1531
01:47:35.616 --> 01:47:37.533
You gave up those things.

1532
01:47:37.618 --> 01:47:41.412
You let go of who you were.
Family. friends. that's the deal.

1533
01:47:42.623 --> 01:47:44.457
Why are we still talking about this?

1534
01:47:44.958 --> 01:47:47.001
Because the agency invested a lot in you.

1535
01:47:47.294 --> 01:47:50.672
And you're an asset
only as long as you stay focused.

1536
01:47:59.640 --> 01:48:00.640
You look good.

1537
01:48:02.142 --> 01:48:03.559
Get some rest.

1538
01:48:03.644 --> 01:48:07.897
We got to transfer you to a secure facility
tomorrow. For your safety.

1539
01:48:14.697 --> 01:48:15.988
(DOOR CLOSES)

1540
01:48:35.551 --> 01:48:38.261
Nurse? What... What did you give me?

1541
01:48:40.180 --> 01:48:41.472
(DISTANTLY) Brotine-zero.

1542
01:48:54.319 --> 01:48:55.486
(WHISPERING) Stay under there. Roy.

1543
01:48:56.947 --> 01:48:58.030
You're dead.

1544
01:49:01.118 --> 01:49:02.702
Make way. please.

1545
01:49:03.287 --> 01:49:04.912
Going to the mortuary.

1546
01:49:08.792 --> 01:49:10.334
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1547
01:49:10.419 --> 01:49:13.129
Don't worry. Roy. I got this.

1548
01:49:14.173 --> 01:49:16.174
It's time for a vacation.

1549
01:49:24.725 --> 01:49:26.350
(RIDE LIKE THE WIND PLAYING ON RADIO)

1550
01:49:26.435 --> 01:49:27.810
JUNE: (SINGING) Ride like the wind

1551
01:49:30.439 --> 01:49:31.898
And I've got

1552
01:49:33.650 --> 01:49:37.820
Such a long way to go
To make it to the border of Mexico

1553
01:49:42.868 --> 01:49:44.535
(WAVES CRASHING)

1554
01:49:44.620 --> 01:49:46.370
(GULLS SQUAWKING)

1555
01:49:46.455 --> 01:49:49.665
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

1556
01:50:21.865 --> 01:50:23.783
Hey. there. sleepy head.

1557
01:50:26.537 --> 01:50:27.787
What day is it?

1558
01:50:28.914 --> 01:50:30.164
Someday.

1559
01:50:31.875 --> 01:50:33.334
Someday. Roy.

1560
01:50:42.761 --> 01:50:44.428
What am I wearing?

1561
01:50:46.932 --> 01:50:48.015
A pair of shorts.

1562
01:50:50.060 --> 01:50:51.811
How did I get into shorts?

1563
01:50:53.647 --> 01:50:56.315
Roy. I've been trained to rebuild
a six-speed transmission

1564
01:50:56.400 --> 01:50:59.235
with nothing but a pair of pliers
and a crescent wrench.

1565
01:51:00.153 --> 01:51:02.780
I think I can get you into a pair
of shorts without looking.

1566
01:51:04.658 --> 01:51:06.492
I'm not saying that's what I did.

1567
01:51:07.995 --> 01:51:10.037
You're both the navigator and the DJ.

1568
01:51:10.122 --> 01:51:12.582
And we have a long way to go
to Cape Horn.

1569
01:51:14.835 --> 01:51:18.170
With me. without me. With me.

1570
01:51:20.090 --> 01:51:21.424
without me.

1571
01:51:22.259 --> 01:51:23.301
With you.

1572
01:51:23.385 --> 01:51:25.928
Put some tunes on the radio. Mr. DJ.

1573
01:51:26.805 --> 01:51:27.847
Yes. ma'am.

1574
01:51:28.098 --> 01:51:30.600
(SOMEDAY PLAYING)

1575
